<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="utf-8" />
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width,initial-scale=1" />
  <title>Why the Capybara? — ParkerPixie</title>
  <meta name="description" content="Why the capybara is my grounding spirit animal, and how Bejeweled the Peacock embodies my glittery, unapologetic side." />

  <!-- Page-scoped styles -->
  <style>
    /* Force the cotton-candy background */
    body {
      background: url("/bg/cotton-candy.jpg") no-repeat center center fixed;
      background-size: cover;
      background-attachment: fixed;
      margin: 0;
      min-height: 100vh;
    }

    :root{
      --brand:#8a5dff;           /* Parker purple */
      --brand-deep:#4026a6;      /* deep purple */
      --gold:#f0c866;            /* soft gold */
      --ink:#1b1335;             /* deep text */
      --ink-soft:#3a3160;
      --card:rgba(255,255,255,0.78);
      --card-blur:10px;
      --ring:rgba(138,93,255,0.35);
    }

    .why-capybara{
      color:var(--ink);
      padding: clamp(16px, 3vw, 32px);
      max-width: 1080px;
      margin: 0 auto;
      line-height: 1.6;
    }

    .why-capybara .hero{
      display:grid;
      gap: 8px;
      margin: clamp(8px, 2vw, 16px) 0 24px;
    }
    .why-capybara .eyebrow{
      text-transform: uppercase;
      letter-spacing: .18em;
      font-size: .8rem;
      color: var(--brand);
      font-weight: 700;
    }
    .why-capybara h1{
      margin: 0;
      font-size: clamp(2rem, 4.2vw, 3.25rem);
      line-height: 1.15;
      letter-spacing: .5px;
      color: var(--ink);
      text-shadow: 0 1px 0 rgba(255,255,255,.35);
    }
    .why-capybara .subtitle{
      color: var(--ink-soft);
      font-size: clamp(1rem, 2.2vw, 1.15rem);
      max-width: 65ch;
    }

    .why-capybara .card{
      background: var(--card);
      backdrop-filter: blur(var(--card-blur));
      border-radius: 18px;
      padding: clamp(16px, 2.5vw, 28px);
      border: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,.6);
      box-shadow:
        0 10px 30px rgba(27,19,53,.08),
        inset 0 0 0 1px rgba(255,255,255,.25);
      margin: 16px 0;
    }

    .why-capybara h2{
      font-size: clamp(1.35rem, 2.8vw, 1.8rem);
      margin: 0 0 10px;
      color: var(--brand-deep);
    }

    .stack{ display:grid; gap: 14px; }

    .callout{
      border-left: 4px solid var(--gold);
      background: rgba(240, 200, 102, 0.12);
      padding: 14px 16px;
      border-radius: 12px;
      font-style: italic;
    }

    .yin-yang{
      display:grid; gap:14px;
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }
    @media (min-width: 800px){
      .yin-yang{ grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; }
    }
    .yy{
      border: 1px dashed var(--ring);
      border-radius: 16px;
      padding: 14px;
      background: rgba(255,255,255,.65);
    }
    .yy h3{
      margin: 0 0 8px;
      font-size: 1.05rem;
      color: var(--brand);
      letter-spacing: .3px;
    }
    .yy ul{ margin: 0; padding-left: 18px; }

    .gallery{
      display:grid;
      gap: 18px;
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
      margin-top: 4px;
    }
    @media (min-width: 720px){
      .gallery{ grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; }
    }
    figure{
      margin: 0;
      background: rgba(255,255,255,.7);
      border-radius: 16px;
      overflow: hidden;
      border: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,.55);
      box-shadow: 0 8px 20px rgba(0,0,0,.05);
    }
    picture, img{
      display:block; width:100%; height:auto;
    }
    figcaption{
      padding: 10px 12px 12px;
      font-size: .95rem;
      color: var(--ink-soft);
    }
    .caption-emoji{ font-size: 1.05rem; margin-right: 6px; }

    .source{
      font-size: .9rem;
      opacity: .8;
    }
    .source a{ color: var(--brand-deep); text-decoration: underline; }
  </style>
</head>
<body>
  <main class="why-capybara" role="main">
    <!-- HERO -->
    <header class="hero">
      <div class="eyebrow">Spirit Animals, Sparkle & Healing</div>
      <h1>Why the Capybara?</h1>
      <p class="subtitle">
        The short answer: she found me. The longer answer: I’m equal parts calm capybara and glittering peacock—grounded and unapologetic—guiding my creativity, recovery, and community.
      </p>
    </header>

    <!-- ... rest of your content stays exactly the same ... -->

  </main>
</body>
</html>
